Reasoning: The paper deals with computational biology and the study of the parameterized complexity of two well-known problems in this field, namely Maximum Agreement SubTree (MAST) and Maximum Compatible Tree (MCT), with respect to the maximum degree of the input trees. The paper uses recent advances in parameterized complexity to obtain tight lower bounds for these problems. The topics covered in the paper are closely related to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), computational complexity (cs.CC), computational geometry (cs.CG), machine learning (cs.LG), and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
